comment_data.body:
Not sure how that could happen since this is later, not earlier. But ye moving it inside the `s->c == K_EVENT` statement doesn't make sense. But then resetting it again here is probably better?
```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/ex_getln.c b/src/nvim/ex_getln.c
index 9f6c47abf5..4a29b1b975 100644
--- a/src/nvim/ex_getln.c
+++ b/src/nvim/ex_getln.c
@@ -1300,6 +1300,7 @@ static int command_line_execute(VimState *state, int key)
   if (ccline.cmdbuff_replaced && s->xpc.xp_numfiles > 0) {
     command_line_end_wildmenu(s, false, -1);
   }
+  ccline.cmdbuff_replaced = false;

   // Skip wildmenu during history navigation via Up/Down keys
   if (s->c == K_WILD && s->did_hist_navigate) {
@@ -1326,8 +1327,8 @@ static int command_line_execute(VimState *state, int key)
     // If f_setcmdline() changed the cmdline treat it as such.
     if (ccline.cmdbuff_replaced) {
       command_line_changed(s);
+      ccline.cmdbuff_replaced = false;
     }
-    ccline.cmdbuff_replaced = false;

     // nvim_select_popupmenu_item() can be called from the handling of
     // K_EVENT, K_COMMAND, or K_LUA.
```

